        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add Pioneer.ai as an inference provider with live model discovery",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nOpenClaw had no support for Pioneer.ai as an inference provider. Users with Pioneer.ai accounts could not use it as a model source, and there was no way to browse or select Pioneer models from the UI model picker.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis PR adds Pioneer.ai as a first-class OpenClaw inference provider with full live model discovery:\n\n- **Pioneer plugin** (`extensions/pioneer/`) registers Pioneer.ai as an OpenAI-compatible provider at `https://api.pioneer.ai/v1`. Authentication uses a `PIONEER_API_KEY` env var or auth profile.\n- **Live model discovery** — Pioneer's `catalog.run` hook calls the Pioneer `/v1/models` endpoint at runtime and merges the full live model list into the catalog. The `pioneer/auto` routing alias (which lets Pioneer route to the best available model automatically) is always preserved in the catalog even though the live API does not return it directly.\n- **Gateway catalog warm** — A new `sidecars.model-catalog-warm` startup sidecar pre-warms the gateway model catalog on startup so the full Pioneer model list is available in the UI picker from the first open. The `models.list` RPC timeout is raised to 30s to survive cold-start warm-up.\n- **Periodic refresh** — The warm sidecar re-runs full discovery every 30 minutes using `markGatewayModelCatalogStaleForReload` so newly added Pioneer models appear automatically without a gateway restart. The loop is error-resilient: a transient API failure logs a warning and retries on the next tick.\n- **Provider wildcard allowlist** — Onboarding sets `pioneer/*` in `agents.defaults.models` so all live-discovered Pioneer models are visible in the picker without enumerating them individually.\n- **Default model** — `pioneer/auto` is set as the default primary at onboard time, routing each request to the best available Pioneer model automatically.\n\n## User Impact\n\n- Users can now add Pioneer.ai as an inference provider and use any of its 78+ models.\n- The UI model picker shows the full live Pioneer model list (~8s on first gateway start, instant on subsequent restarts from sidecar cache).\n- New Pioneer models appear automatically within 30 minutes of being published to the Pioneer API — no gateway restart needed.\n- `pioneer/auto` as the default model means users get the best Pioneer model without manually selecting one.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Pioneer API at `https://api.pioneer.ai/v1/models` returns 78+ models verified live\n- `extensions/pioneer/provider-catalog.test.ts` covers live catalog building, static-only model injection, and ID normalization\n- `extensions/pioneer/index.test.ts` covers plugin registration and onboard config\n- Tested locally: web UI model picker shows full Pioneer catalog after gateway restart with `PIONEER_API_KEY` set",
        "branch": "feat/pioneer-live-model-discovery",
